      "role": "user",
      "content": "hey just thinking about my supplement routine for the winter since it's so dark here in oslo. i was reading that some people take like 50,000 IU of vitamin d every day for a few weeks to really kickstart their immune system and fix a deficiency fast. do u think that's a safe way to do it? i dont want to wait months for it to kick in",
